<HEAD2>(Calculating Percentages\percentages)
<p>   
To calculate percentages,  use the multiplication (*) 
function and the percentage (%) function.  For example,
to determine the number that is 45
percent of 250, follow these steps:
<list>(numbered)
<le>Enter 250. The number 250 appears in the
accumulator.
<le>Enter *.
<le>Enter 45. The number 45 appears in the accumulator.
<le>Enter %. The result, 112.5, appears in the
accumulator.
<endlist>

<P>
